<p>Assuming that the Sm-A–Hex-B phase transition lies in a crossover region between the mean field (tricritial behavior) and the 3D XY universality class, Aharony et al. [
 <xref rid="B39-materials-12-03464" ref-type="bibr">39</xref>,
 <xref rid="B40-materials-12-03464" ref-type="bibr">40</xref>] have shown that the BO parameters 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm127">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>C</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mn>6</mn>
       <mi>m</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> for 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm128">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>m</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mn>2</mn>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mo>…</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> satisfy the scaling relation, called the multicritical scaling theory (MCST) Equation (16):
 <disp-formula id="FD17-materials-12-03464">
  <label>(16)</label>
  <math id="mm129">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>C</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mn>6</mn>
       <mi>m</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msup>
      <mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>C</mi>
          <mn>6</mn>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mo>)</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>σ</mi>
        <mi>m</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where the exponent 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm130">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>σ</mi>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is Equation (17):
 <disp-formula id="FD18-materials-12-03464">
  <label>(17)</label>
  <math id="mm131">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>σ</mi>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mi>m</mi>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>x</mi>
      <mi>m</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>·</mo>
     <mi>m</mi>
     <mo>·</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>m</mi>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mn>1</mn>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>.</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
